#80000
An Austere, Stone Foyer~
While small, this room has an air of spaciousness belying it's size

because of the near complete lack of adornment in it.  Other than the

cold, undecorated stone benches chiseled from the wall on each side of

the room, there is very little to catch the eye.  There is a door

directly in the middle of the south wall, with no door handle, lock, or

obvious method of opening.  To the north is a similarly bleak portal,

with a small arrowslit at eye level to a vyan to distinguish it.  The

ceilings also have murder-holes in them, making it much easier to decide

where the scarring and pitting of the floor came from.

~
